definitions.definition: A member of a group of Han Chinese whose traditional ancestral homes are in southern Fujian, South China.
( obsolete ) A member of a Southern Min -speaking Chinese people who inhabit or originate from eastern Guangdong ; ( loosely ) Teochew .

main_definition: A member of a group of Han Chinese whose traditional ancestral homes are in southern Fujian, South China.
secondary_definitions: ( obsolete ) A member of a Southern Min -speaking Chinese people who inhabit or originate from eastern Guangdong ; ( loosely ) Teochew .

definitions.definition: Taiwanese , the variety of Hokkien spoken in Taiwan and the native language of the Hoklo.
A variety of Southern Min Chinese originating from the Hailufeng region.

main_definition: Taiwanese , the variety of Hokkien spoken in Taiwan and the native language of the Hoklo.
secondary_definitions: ( Hong Kong ) A variety of Southern Min Chinese originating from the Hailufeng region.
